The global Fiberoptic Phototherapy Equipment market is experiencing a surge in demand due to the rising prevalence of skin disorders and neonatal jaundice. Fiberoptic phototherapy equipment utilizes light to treat various skin conditions effectively. The market growth is driven by advancements in technology, increasing healthcare expenditure, and growing awareness about skin health. Moreover, the rising number of preterm births globally is further fueling the demand for fiberoptic phototherapy equipment for neonatal care. Additionally, the rising geriatric population prone to skin diseases is boosting market growth as well. With ongoing research and development activities to enhance the efficiency and effectiveness of fiberoptic phototherapy equipment, the market is anticipated to witness substantial growth in the coming years.

